\par\pard\plain \tx235\tx720\li576\fi-216\sa60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext	\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 Show the reader that, while this may not be true love, this is a lovely connection between these two.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 At this point, the reader probably thinks that this is going to be a typical romance and that Maggie and Evan are going to end the novel together. I'm okay with leaving them with that impression for now.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 However, we are going to trickle in Chloe here. Although the rest of the office decorated is modern photography and motivational business posters, the conference room there dining in is the one exception in the core. Liz has proudly hung up Chloe's "triptyct" paintings. Maggie notices them and comments on how beautiful they are. Evan agrees, having no idea that Chloe, who he had yet to meet, will one day be his true love.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 Show the reader a glimpse of how Evan perceives his role as "World's Best Boyfriend" will play out. He has gone out of his way to meet every one of Maggie's needs.<!$Scr_Ps::6>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sl168\slmult1\ltrch\loch \f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf1
